title.en: CS:GO: ESL Pro League Finals - Odense

desc.en: ESL Pro League season 6 finals comes to Sparekassen Fyn Arena in Odense, Denmark from 8. - 10. december. The twelve best CS:GO teams from Europe and North America will battle it out for a total prize pool of US $1 million. The participating teams are Astralis, FaZe clan, Fnatic, Hellraisers, Ninjas in Pyjamas, North, Luminosity Gaming, Misfits, NRG Esports, OpTic Gaming, SK Gaming and Team Liquid.

The 12 best teams from North America and Europe (6 from each region) will compete in a three-day tournament to determine the best Vainglory team in the West. Going on from May 19-21. See all the pros play in front of a live audience, at the legendary O2 in London, UK. The 2017 Spring Championship is the first time both NA and EU teams will compete at the same regional championship

DOTA 2 ESL One is back this time from Katowice, Poland. Sixteen teams from across the globe will fight for a part of the $1,000,000 USD prize. The playoffs will be held on February 24-25, 2018 at the Spodek Arena. This is from day 4, the Quarterfinal.

title.en: World of Tanks: WGL The Grand Finals

desc.en: Wargaming.net League: The Grand Finals 2017 is the largest eSports tournament in the World of Tanks calendar, which annually gathers pro players and teams from the CIS, Europe, North America and Asia to fight for the title of world champion. The Grand Finals playoffs takes place from 27 to 28 May in Moscow.
